    <h1>Sending newsletters</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This page of the manual describes which settings you need to carry out to send newsletters with plentymarkets. Use the newsletter function that is <a href="/en/crm/sending-newsletters#100">integrated in plentymarkets</a> or send your newsletters with <a href="/en/crm/sending-newsletters#1700">CleverReach</a> or <a href="/en/crm/sending-newsletters#2100">Newsletter2Go</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The double opt-in method is used in plentymarkets. This means that the recipient will be sent an email after having asked to receive the newsletter. This email contains a link that is used to confirm the newsletter subscription. Customers will only receive the newsletter after they have clicked on the link. This method is integrated in plentymarkets and cannot be changed.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="100">1. Setting up the newsletter service integrated in plentymarkets</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to set up the newsletter service that is integrated in plentymarkets. You have to carry out settings in multiple menus in order to be able to send newsletters with plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="200">1.1. Entering newsletter access data</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to <strong>System » Client » Select client » Email » Newsletter</strong>. Enter the access data to use the newsletter service that is integrated in plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Entering newsletter access data:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Client » Select client » Email » Newsletter</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-newsletter-access-data">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
