<h3 id="800">1.7. Linking the email template to the double opt-in function</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the next step, link the email template that you have just created to the double opt-in function and select another template for the option <strong>Newsletter opt-in confirmation</strong>. If you use the double opt-in method, the customer has to confirm the newsletter registration after he or she has registered for the newsletter.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Notes about the double opt-in method</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You must <a href="/en/crm/sending-newsletters#700">create</a> two templates and select these for the events Newsletter opt-in and <strong>Newsletter opt-in confirmation</strong> in the <strong>System » Client » Select client » Email » Automatic email</strong> menu. The selected template under <strong>Newsletter opt-in</strong> will be sent when the customer has registered for the newsletter. This template should contain the confirmation link that the customer has to click in order to complete the newsletter registration. Use the template variable <strong>$NewsletterConfirmURL</strong> to display the confirmation link. This template variable contains the URL to confirm the newsletter registration. The selected template under <strong>Newsletter opt-in confirmation</strong> will be sent when the customer has activated the confirmation link.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the customer data record in the <strong>CRM » Edit customers » Search customer » Open customer</strong> menu, the <strong>Newsletter</strong> option will be activated automatically in the <strong>Customer data</strong> tab when the customer has registered for the newsletter during the order process and has confirmed the newsletter registration via the confirmation link.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Linking the email template to the double opt-in function:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Client » Select client » Email » Automatic email</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the email template that was previously created from the <strong>Newsletter opt-in</strong> drop-down menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the email template that was previously created from the <strong>Newsletter opt-in confirmation</strong> drop-down menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can see the confirmation status by going to <strong>System » CMS » Newsletter » plentymarkets » Emails</strong>. Customers who confirmed that they want to receive the newsletter are designated with the status <strong>confirmed</strong>. Customers who did not go through the double opt-in process are designated with the status <strong>not confirmed</strong>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="900">1.8. Saving an email address</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The email addresses that newsletters should be sent to are saved in various folders. Go to <strong>System » CMS » Newsletter » plentymarkets » Emails</strong> to manage the email addresses that are saved in these folders. If you have not yet created a <a href="/en/crm/sending-newsletters#300">folder structure</a> for your newsletters, then we recommend doing so before you continue.</p>
</div>
