<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="1100">1.10. Searching for customers by their email address or surname</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to save an email address in an email folder. You can either search for customers by their email address or by their surname.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Searching for customers by their email address or surname:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » CMS » Newsletter » plentymarkets » Emails</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Expand the email folder.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the option <strong>Email address</strong> or <strong>Surname</strong> from the drop-down menu. Customers will be searched for by this criterion.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the customer’s email address or surname in the search field. <br>
→ It is sufficient to only enter part of the name or email address. Leave the field blank if you want to display all email addresses or surnames.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Search</strong>.<br>
→ The search result(s) will be displayed.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The confirmation status is also displayed in the search results. The <a href="/en/crm/sending-newsletters#800">double opt-in method</a> is used in plentymarkets. This means that the recipient is sent an email after having asked to receive the newsletter. This email contains a link that is used to confirm the newsletter subscription. Customers who confirmed that they want to receive the newsletter are designated with the status <strong>confirmed</strong>. Otherwise, you will see the words <strong>not confirmed</strong>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="1200">1.11. Editing an email address</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Once you have found an email address with the search function, you can edit the data that is saved for this customer. For example, this is useful if you need to update a customer’s email address or if you want to move the customer data record into a different email folder. To do so, proceed as follows.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Editing an email address:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » CMS » Newsletter » plentymarkets » Emails</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search for the customer as described in the chapter <a href="/en/crm/sending-newsletters#1100">Searching for customers by their email address or surname</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Expand the customer.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the changes as desired. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-save-email-address">Table 4</a> in the <a href="/en/crm/sending-newsletters#900">Saving an email address</a> chapter.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="1300">1.12. Exporting and importing email addresses</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The previous chapters describe how to manage individual email addresses. If you want to edit several email addresses at once, then it is recommended that you work with the <a href="/en/basics/data-exchange">data exchange</a>. You can import or export email addresses. You can export all of the email addresses by going to <a href="/en/basics/data-exchange/exporting-data">Data » Dynamic export</a> and using the <a href="/en/basics/data-exchange/data-formats/customernewsletter">CustomerNewsletter</a> data format. You can import new email addresses by going to <a href="/en/basics/data-exchange/importing-data">Data » Dynamic import</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
