<h2 id="2100">3. Sending newsletters with Newsletter2Go</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to send newsletters to your customers with <a href="https://www.newsletter2go.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Newsletter2Go</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">SOAP module is required to use Newsletter2Go</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Please note that you require the SOAP module in order to use the Newsletter2Go service. The SOAP module allows for correct data retrieval.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="2200">3.1. Registering with Newsletter2Go</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Register for free in order to use Newsletter2Go in plentymarkets. To do so, go to the <a href="https://www.newsletter2go.co.uk/registration/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Newsletter2Go website</a>. For further information about the settings in Newsletter2Go, refer to the Newsletter2Go <a href="https://www.newsletter2go.co.uk/help/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">help</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="2300">3.2. Creating a user</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to <a href="/en/basics/working-with-plentymarkets/manage-users#10">System » Settings » User » Accounts</a> to create a new user for Newsletter2Go. You will need this user for the Newsletter2Go interface. When creating the user with the user class <strong>Newsletter2Go</strong>, all rights required for the SOAP API will be automatically saved. These rights include for example the setting <strong>Customer</strong> for the recipient’s synchronisation as well as the setting <strong>Item</strong> for the item transfer.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a user:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Open the menu <strong>System » Settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>New</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the <strong>User name</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the <strong>Actual name</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select <strong>Newsletter2Go</strong> from the <strong>User class</strong> drop-down menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a <strong>password</strong> (twice).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="2400">3.3. Setting up a user</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the next step, you set up the new user for Newsletter2Go.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting up a user:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Open the menu <strong>System » Settings » User » Accounts</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the Newsletter2Go user that you have just created.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Right</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Visibility</strong> tab, select the clients (stores) in the <strong>Client (store)</strong> section.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Sending newsletters from an exclusive, dedicated IP address</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can send your Newsletter2Go newsletters from an <a href="https://www.newsletter2go.com/features/newsletter-dispatch-dedicated-ips/">exclusive, dedicated IP address</a>. To use this service, you need to access the Service centre in the <strong>Start » Service centre</strong> menu and save the Newsletter2Go <a href="/en/basics/arbeiten-mit-plentymarkets/plentymarkets-konto#domain-nameserver">name server</a> for the sub-domains. You will receive the necessary information regarding the sub-domains and name server from Newsletter2Go.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
